news.title: Omaxe to invest Rs 2,500 crore to develop projects under new brand
news.para: Omaxe's new brand will focus on joint ventures, collaboration and development through public-private partnerships (PPP).

news.title: Arvind SmartSpaces to develop 440 acre industrial park in Ahmedabad
news.para: Arvind SmartSpaces' industrial park project has a total estimated area of about 440 acre and a top-line potential of Rs 1,350 crore.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government to grant house sites only to BPL families
news.para: Special chief secretary (revenue) RP Sisodia on Monday released detailed guidelines for the implementation of ‘Housing for All' programme.

news.title: Saudi Arabia allows foreigners to invest in firms with property in Mecca and Medina
news.para: The move will allow foreigners to invest in firms whose revenues rely on the Islamic pilgrimage, one of the top revenue sources for the oil-rich kingdom.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body to collect Rs 200 crore from flat and plot owners in Vaishali
news.para: Among other proposals, the board deferred the implementation of mandatory structural audits for multi-storey buildings until discussions were held with members of Credai — an umbrella of developers.

news.title: RBI supersedes board of Aviom India Housing Finance over governance, payment defaults
news.para: The Reserve Bank has appointed Ram Kumar, ex-CGM of Punjab National Bank, as the Administrator of the New Delhi-based company.

news.title: Noida International airport set to launch on April 17
news.para: Officials said on Monday that the flooring of the terminal building is complete, and escalators and baggage handling systems have been installed.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh govt launches OTS scheme to resolve 1,400 stamp duty cases
news.para: Currently, there are 1,400 stamp duty cases pending in four courts in the district. The scheme aims to resolve pending cases swiftly and boost state revenue, officials said.

news.title: Equinox India appoints Jitendra Virwani as non-executive non-independent director
news.para: Equinox India has also completed allotment of 60,91,05,999 fully paid equity shares, to the shareholders of NAM Estates, in accordance with the merger scheme.

news.title: Bajaj Housing Finance's net profit up 25.41% in Q3 FY25
news.para: Bajaj Housing Finance's total income stood at Rs 2,448.98 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 25.83% from Rs 1,946.29 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Bombay HC suggests Lodha brothers settle dispute over trademark amicably
news.para: The Abhishek Lodha-promoted Macrotech Developers Ltd earlier this month filed a suit in the HC against Abhinandan Lodha's real estate firm, House of Abhinandan Lodha, claiming the name 'Lodha' was their trademark and no one else could use it.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh govt to hand over keys to 1.14 lakh housing scheme beneficiaries
news.para: All the ministers, legislators and ruling party leaders have been asked to kick-start the programme in their constituencies soon after the CM launched the programme.

news.title: Residents of seven villages pass resolutions opposing merger with Trichy civic body
news.para: The municipal administration department already passed a govt order approving the expansion of Trichy corporation by increasing the existing 65 wards to 100 wards.

news.title: ACC posts net profit of Rs 1,091.79 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: ACC's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 6,575.62 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 31.50 per cent from Rs 5,000.51 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: China Vanke's chairman and CEO resign amid liquidity concerns
news.para: Xin Jie, the chairman of its major state-owned shareholder Shenzhen Metro, will become Vanke's chairman, signalling increased state oversight on expectations that the government would step in to contain non-repayment risks.

news.title: Dubai's rapid growth putting strains on its residents
news.para: The city-state has seen record-breaking real estate transactions and as more and more people come to live there, and its state-owned airline Emirates is booking record earnings. But all that growth comes with strains for the city's population.

news.title: Allahabad HC rejects farmer’s petition for 4% additional developed land
news.para: The petitioner, Ram Beer Singh, sought an additional 4% developed land based on a 2011 full-bench judgment in the Gajraj case.

news.title: NGT issues notice to MoEF, Haryana and Rajasthan officials over Aravali hill flattening
news.para: In its order on Jan 22, the NGT bench of chairperson Prakash Shrivastava and expert member Dr Afroz Ahmad said that the report raised "apprehensions" regarding widespread illegal mining. that culminated in the collapse of an Aravali hillock along the Haryana-Rajasthan border.

news.title: Brookfield closes two real estate investments in Japan for $1.6 billion
news.para: The investments comprise a stake in Tokyo's landmark Gajoen complex, a mixed-use office, retail and luxury hotel, and a 1 million square foot (93,000 square metre) plot in the outskirts of Nagoya, which will be developed into a logistics warehouse, Brookfield said in a release.

news.title: Over 500 acres of BMTC land left open to encroachment: CAG report
news.para: The issue dates back to 2008 when the BMTC board, in its 52nd meeting, acknowledged its land holdings and took initial steps to protect vacant plots.
